description: Slave camera or endline camera was not showing the specific scoreboard for this fixture. The device got stuck in IDLE state and was not updating the score for the fixture. To try to fix this issue, the device was restarted using Troy, then an execute command was sent, but after this step the device appears as Disconnected and not reporting Telemetry, and when it did, it continues to be stuck on IDLE state. This step was repeated a few times. Then, Help videostreaming support was contacted to take over the issue., and they mentioned that Execute command from hermes was sending a wrong format overlay url and probably causing the phone to restart. Commands were send by hand using bartolomeo taking the information from the bundle of commands in hermes. This issue was fixed when the match was approximately on 1 hour 20 minutes.

The Genius Support team was making the validations before the game however it was not possible to access to the phone. 


In order to access the phone: 

1. Contacted POC and requested to open the host app. 

2. Validated the internet connection 

3. Restarted the device. 


After all the attempts were not possible to access. So it was requested to the POC open LISA manually in order to start the streaming. The streaming was ongoing and the signal was lost in two opportunities. 


Also, the scoreboard was not working properly for 15 minutes, the phone was not receiving the commands that the Genius support team was sending through Bartolomeo. Considering that it was not possible to access the phone, it was requested to the POC to open and close Lisa's app manually.

This situation was solved by finding the phone that was doing the streaming and stopping it.
